Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "struju" in different forms and positions:

1. *Struja* je nestala tokom oluje. (The power went out during the storm.)
2. Moramo da platimo račun za *struju* do kraja meseca. (We have to pay the electricity bill by the end of the month.)
3. *Strujanje* vode je veoma jako u ovom delu reke. (The water flow is very strong in this part of the river.)
4. Kada stavite prst u utičnicu, osetićete *strujni* udar. (When you put your finger in the socket, you'll feel an electric shock.)
5. Preduzeće je uložilo mnogo novca u obnovu *električne struje* u ovom delu grada. (The company invested a lot of money in the renovation of electrical power in this part of the city.)
6. Da biste uključili svetlo, morate da pritisnete dugme koje će pustiti *struju*. (To turn on the light, you have to press the button that will let the electricity flow.)
7. Našao sam novi način da koristim *strujni* krug i uštedim energiju. (I found a new way to use the electric circuit and save energy.)

*Note: The word "struju" is highlighted with a star (*) in each sentence.* 

I hope this helps!